<h1>
Building with Borland C++ 5.02 and prior
</h1>
<p>
The Borland C++ integrated development environment cannot be configured
to build using BullseyeCoverage due to limitations of Borland C++.
However, you can build from the command prompt using a makefile as described
below.
<p>
In the integrated development environment, create a makefile from
your project using the command <code>Project Generate makefile</code>.
To ensure the generated makefile is correct, go to the command prompt
and build the project without BullseyeCoverage as shown below.
<PRE>
cov01 -0
erase *.obj
make -f project.mak
</PRE>
<P>
The integrated development environment often creates an invalid makefile.
For assistance correcting the makefile, contact Borland Technical Support.
After you have the makefile functioning correctly,
rebuild the project with BullseyeCoverage as shown below.
<PRE>
cov01 -1
erase *.obj
make -f project.mak
</PRE>

